race.comment: Wide open. COSTLESS (1) has been going well and has the ratings to beat these. Fourth in town two back then raced on speed from a wide gate in the south-east and scored an impressive win. Tricky gate but with the majority here getting back can slide across and give a sight again. SASSY ANGEL (12) was outclassed in town two back then just missed behind Shuttle Run at Clare. That galloper and the third placegetter are in race six. Peaks for this and will be winding up late again. STAR VALOUR (6) resumed from almost a year off with a win at Lock. Will surely be fitter for it and returns to home track. Have to include again. LION'S INSTINCT (7) was a fresh-up winner at Clare and has scope for more. Drawn for a soft run and will charge late. HE'S ABEL (9) was thereabouts at Lock but will strip much fitter. Has a poor second-up record but is very well weighted in this with the claim and knows his way around this circuit.
